  "texts": [
    "[55] found that messages framed to match audience ideology were more effective.",
    "Costello et al. [44] demonstrated that real-time adaptation of message content-based on participants' expressed beliefs-could enhance engagement in interactive settings.",
    "Together, these studies show how LLMs support the design of experiments that incorporate treatment heterogeneity from the outset, reducing the need for post hoc subgroup analysis.",
    "In another study, Coppolillo et al. [45] trained a LLM to generate content that dynamically adapts to the opinion distribution within a social network.",
    "Rather than producing generic messages, the model learns to tailor its output to maximize engagement in specific social contexts, demonstrating a scalable approach to context-sensitive stimulus generation."
